1 SECTION 2. Chapter 603, Hawaii Revised Statutes, is
2 amended by adding a new section to be appropriately designated
3 and to read as follows:
4 "§603- Women's court program; first circuit. (a)
5 There shall be established within the first circuit of the
6 judiciary the women's court program. The program shall
7 implement trauma-informed and evidence-based practices, employ
8 gender-responsive programming, collaborate with stakeholders,
9 and provide services to women in the court system with the goal
10 of diverting participants from incarceration, supporting their
11 success in the community, and reducing recidivism.
12 (b) The services offered by the program shall address the
13 following areas:
14 (1) Trauma and mental health treatment;
15 (2) Family support, including parenting, education, and
16 relationship improvement;
17 (3) Life-skills training;
18 (4) Education and vocational training;
19 (5) Domestic violence prevention;
20 (6) Medical services and health education;
21 (7) Substance abuse detection, prevention, and treatment;
