1 (8) Mentoring; and
2 (9) Housing support."
3 PART III
4 SECTION 3. (a) There shall be established within the
5 third circuit Kona division of the judiciary the women's court
6 pilot program. The women's court pilot program shall be under
7 the supervision of the big island drug court. The judiciary
8 shall be responsible for providing mental health services under
9 this pilot program. The pilot program shall implement trauma-
10 informed and evidence-based practices, employ gender-responsive
11 programming, collaborate with stakeholders, and provide services
12 to women in the court system with the goal of diverting
13 participants from incarceration, supporting their success in the
14 community, and reducing recidivism.
15 (b) The services offered by the pilot program shall
16 address the following areas:
17 (1) Trauma and mental health treatment;
18 (2) Family support, including parenting, education, and
19 relationship improvement;
20 (3) Life-skills training;
21 (4) Education and vocational training;
