4 (8) Mentoring; and
5 (9) Housing support.
6 SECTION 4. The judiciary shall submit a report of its
7 findings and recommendations, including any proposed
8 legislation, on the pilot program to the governor and
9 legislature no later than forty days prior to the convening of
10 the regular sessions of 2026 and 2027, regarding:
11 (1) The status of the women's court pilot program;
12 (2) The number of women accepted into the women's court
13 pilot program;
14 (3) The number of women who were eligible to participate
15 in the women's court pilot program but who could not
16 be accepted into the pilot program because of pilot
17 program limitations;
18 (4) The number of women completing the women's court pilot
19 program;
20 (5) The number of women who were removed from the women's
21 court pilot program; and
