1 (6) Recommendations as to whether the women's court pilot
2 program should:
3 (A) Continue as a pilot program;
4 (B) Expand to include additional participants;
5 (C) Provide additional services; or
6 (D) Be discontinued.
7 SECTION 5. There is appropriated out of the general
8 revenues of the State of Hawaii the sum of $514,900 or so much
9 thereof as may be necessary for fiscal year 2025-2026 and
10 $557,000 or so much thereof as may be necessary for fiscal year
11 2026-2027 for mental health, substance abuse treatment, and
12 other services and equipment, and the establishment of one full-
13 time equivalent (1.0 FTE) temporary Kona drug court probation
14 supervisor position for the women's court pilot program
15 established pursuant to section 3 of this Act.
16 The sums appropriated shall be expended by the judiciary
17 for the purposes of this Act.
18 PART IV
19 SECTION 6. This Act shall take effect on July 1, 2025;
20 provided that part III shall be repealed on June 30, 2027.
